<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-474-974  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 474 974.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  May 1 1990 v29 n9 p96(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Single-function embedded controller key to maximum efficiency.andO;(Cirrus Logic developmental process)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Wishneusky, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Cirrus Logic found that a strategy of designing and tailoring anembedded processor for a single-chip, intelligent communicationscontroller to a single application reduced the amount andcomplexity of support logic required to meet the goals of highefficiency and high throughput at standard serial bit rates.andP;  Thedesign specifications also required an architecture that could beevolved to support other protocols, would be easy to modify andupgrade, and supported a large number of channels at a low costper channel.andP;  The resulting multitasking processor couldefficiently handle multichannel data communications processes andfeatured a reduced-instruction-set level of complexity,one-clock-per-instruction execution rate, load-store andregister-based architecture, memory-mapped input/output processingand very fast context-switch time.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Cirrus Logic Inc. (product development).andO;Ticker:    CRUS.andO;Topic:     Communications CircuitsProduct DevelopmentSpecificationsCriteriaGoals and ObjectivesSystem DesignEmbedded SystemsMicroprocessorsControllers.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>